Investigators: Fleur Visser
SiteName: Lakeside Campus, University of Worcester
community_description: The site was sown at some unknown point in the relatively recent past, using a pasture-mixture. It therefore isn’t really possible to exactly define the plant community, but by using the British National Vegetation Classification (NVC) it would be pretty close to the MG6-community. The MG6 is a mesotrophic grassland community which is a well-drained permanent pasture or meadow. In this community there are 6 constant species (species always found), in our plot we have 4 of these 6 species (Festuca rubra, Holcus lanatus, Lolium perenne, Trifolium repens but not Cerastium fontanum or Cynosurus cristatus), also note here that 3 of the 4 constant species we have are the most abundant of all our species (not Holcus lanatus because we only had a few individuals).
